## Git Safety Rules

- Git read operations (log, diff, status, show, branch -l, tag -l, etc.) are always allowed.
- NEVER commit, tag, create branches, reset, or perform any write git operation without explicit user approval — even in Act mode.
- NEVER push to remotes. The user will always handle pushes.
- NEVER commit directly to main/default branch unless explicitly instructed to.
- Don't add tags unless told. There are workflows that do that.
- ALWAYS ask before executing any git write command.

## Project-Specific Rules

### Terraform Documentation Auto-Generation

- The `.github/workflows/pr.yml` workflow runs `terraform-docs` to auto-generate documentation
- Content between `<!-- BEGIN_TF_DOCS -->` and `<!-- END_TF_DOCS -->` tags in README.md is auto-generated
- **Never manually edit content between these tags** — changes will be overwritten by the workflow
- Only edit the user-facing documentation section above these tags

### Module Development Best Practices

- Always set attributes that have provider defaults to match those defaults in module code
- Use `optional(type, default_value)` pattern for variables to avoid unnecessary drift
- Keep module variables flexible but sensible with appropriate defaults